Title: 2008 Subaru Impreza WRX STI - New Motor
Neighborhood: Kirkland eastside
Ad Text Content: We are selling this very clean 2008 STI Hatchback with 71k miles on the body and a BRAND NEW ENGINE from Subaru.  We took this vehicle in with a blown motor and decided to do an entire rebuild on the mechanical and cosmetic parts. We had the motor professionally rebuilt with receipts using OEM parts as well as many additional service items completed at the same time.  Things to note: Brand new all season tires A brand new short block from Subaru included with a 1 yr/12 month warranty Brand new OEM Heads and valves Brand new OEM clutch kit Resurfaced flywheel Brand new step-colder iridium spark plugs Brand new Transmission and differential fluid change Brand new gaskets including head gaskets, valve seals, intake, and exhaust manifold gaskets Brand new OEM size turbo Brand new OEM oil pump, oil cooler, water pump, thermostat, and timing belt Brand new valve cover gasket Brand new Secondary Air Pump New OEM Intake box and hoses New PCV valves New Starter 4x Rebuilt injectors New MAF sensor Brand new shift linkage bushings   This car has no modification except for ta tame muffler delete. No aftermarket intake or performance parts. No engine or interior modifications at all.  We just had the cosmetics gone over as well. We had the headlights resurfaced and re-sprayed with a clear coat. We just had the STI paint corrected and touched up professionally all around and it looks fantastic. All four wheels were just resurfaced, repainted and looks brand new! Foglights are new and we replaced them with amber bulbs.   Can provide anyone interested with a copy of the CarFax. The Subaru holds a CLEAN TITLE and the CarFax sports regular service history. We can provide the new owner with receipts for everything including the engine rebuild.  There is not a cleaner STI Hatchback for sale in the PNW.  We are asking $24700 for this beautiful fully sorted stock STI Hatch.

Title: Ford Expedition 1997 Sport utility truck/suv
Neighborhood: Snoqualmie valley eastside
Ad Text Content: So I'll start with the bad.  It is a missing lug on the front left and the tires could be better and then Clean it!!    The drivers window needs the regulator installed and the new part in ready to be installed.   For those that don't know that means some time working on the install for that window assembly .  The new part comes with the deal.  It Didn't have a muffler when I bought it and still doesn't  however it's  not loud at all.  It        "needed"     brakes on the front end to avoid disaster :-)   That work is done?!!  They have maybe 500 miles on them with absolutely no problem.  Stereo works but the speaker that's in the driver side door isn't a fit. AC was overhauled mid summer for a boat trip to the Gorge for a 3 day run and it towed fabulously.  The toe was for a 22 foot runabout ski boat heavily loaded for fun and it went perfect coming and going from Snoqualmie to Quincy and back and the trailer lights functioned perfectly.  This is in Snoqualmie and the location for the paperwork is in the Safeway parking lot in North bend the ladies are fabulous at expediting and helping!  If I find any time I'll keep cleaning and the like but that's not likely.
